sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1073035
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Inducible ampR expression combined with RhlR, LasI and eforRed expression cassettes
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The parts for this construct were derived from the 2013 distribution kit and the iGEM Team Uppsala.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This construct is the basis for a Quorum sensing system for two bacteria. The selection marker (amp-resistance) is induced by a RhlI(inducer)/RhlR(activator) complex. The RhlR is encoded on the construct itself, whereas the RhlI is taken up from the media. Furthermore the LasI synthetase is expressed to synthesize the autoinducer LasI for the corresponding system in another cell (BBa_K1073034). By the activation of the amp-resistance the gene of interest (in this case the chromoprotein eforRed) is expressed. Together with BBa_K1073034 the construct forms a dependency between two cells (one with BBa_K10733034, the other with BBa_K1073035).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Braunschweig 2013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1073028
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Inducible ampicillin resistance cassette + RhlR expression cassette
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The biobricks for this part were taken from the 2013 distribution kit.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: In complex with the inducer N-butyryl-HSL, the activator RhlR binds to the Rhl promoter and enables expression. This construct provides all the parts required to express the gene behind the rhl promoter. Only the inducer N-butyryl-HSL is missing, which usually is taken up from the media. By the regulation of the inducer's concentration in the media, the expression rate of the gene of interest (in this case ampicillin beta-lactamase) can be controlled.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Braunschweig 2013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1073032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Autoinducer synthase LasI + LVA with combined eforRed chromoprotein expression cassette
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The biobricks for this part were derived from the 2013 distribution kit and the iGEM Team Uppsala.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the basis for the expression of the Las auto inducer synthetase, which synthesizes LasI [N-(3-oxododecanoyl)-homoserine lactone]. LasI binds to the activator LasR. Together they activate the Las promoter. A constitutive expression of the chromoprotein eforRed is added to the construct in order to varify the expression of LasI synthetase. The construct has no promoter in front of the LasI synthetase gene. Therefore the user can choose the promoter himself (e.g. constitutive, induced, repressed, etc.)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Braunschweig 2013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1073011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Inducible ampicillin resistance cassette (regulated by RhlR + N-buturyl-HSL)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is a combination of BBa_K1073001 and BBa_K1073000, which themselves were constructed from biobricks of the 2013 distribution kit.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The promoter for this beta-lactonase is induced by N-(butyryl)-homoserine lactone. Therefore the expression of the ampicillin beta-lactonase is inducable by Rhl Inducer N-(butyryl)-homoserine lactone.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Braunschweig 2013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1073014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Constitutively expressed transcription regulator RhlR + LVA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is a combination of the BBa_K1073006 and BBa_C0071.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The RhlR synthetase is constitutively expressed by a strong promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Braunschweig 2013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1073018
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Autoinducer synthetase LasI ( producing N-3-oxododecanoyl-HSL) with RBS and double terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The part is a combination of BBa_B0032, BBa_C0078, and BBa_B0015, which were taken from the 2013 distribution kit.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: To the lasI protein, which produces the chemical signal AI-1, a RBS and a double terminator was added to facilitate the construction of an expression system.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Braunschweig 2013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1073022
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is a combination of BBa_K1073006 and BBa_K592012, which were derived from the 2013 distribution kit and the iGEM Team Uppsala.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The chromoprotein eforRed is constitutively expressed and can be used for the marking of cells for easier differentiation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Braunschweig 2013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ampR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The part was derived from BBa_P1002 ampicillin resistance cassette. The sequence for the beta-lactamase was gained by PCR of the original BBa_P1002 with appropiate primers.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This sequence codes for a beta-lactamase, which degrades ampicillin. There is no RBS or other information attached, only the sequence for the enzyme plus prefix and suffix.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The primer sequences can be found on iGEM Team Braunschweig's wiki.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Braunschweig 2013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pRhl + RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Inducible promoter of the rhl quorum sensing system with RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Combined construct from BBa_R0071 and BBa_B0032, which were taken from the 2013 distribution kit.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This construct is derived from BBa_R0071 and B0032. It combines the rhl induced promoter with an RBS and can be used to clone it in front of a desired gene of interest, which shall be induced by rhl.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Braunschweig 2013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1073006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is a combination of BBa_J23106 and BBa_B0032, which were taken from 2013 distribution kit.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part combines a constitutive promoter with an RBS and can be cloned in front of a gene of interest. It is a combination of BBa_J23106 and BBa_B0032.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Braunschweig 2013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: lasI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: autoinducer synthetase for PAI from Pseudomonas aeruginosa
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: coding region for lasI protein, which produces the chemical signal AI-1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chris Walsh (Fighting Darwins)

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: rhlR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: rhlR repressor/activator from P. aeruginosa PA3477 (+LVA)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional regulator, in complex with N-butyryl-HSL, RhlR binds to the Rhl promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: (1/28/04 Edit Jamboree) (0) No BB sites (1) ATG (2) TAATAA (3) Blast checks out (4) No codon changes (5) Maybe chassis compatability (check by experiment) (6) Codon usage not optimal (but looks OK) (7) ssrA tag added
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Debra Lin, Srini Devadas, David Gray, Ronny Krashinsky, and Chris Zheng Liu, Boopers

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: eforRed
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This chromoprotein eforRed naturally exhibits red color when expressed. The color is weaker than RFP, however. On agar plates and in liquid culture, the color is readily visible to naked eye in less than 24 hours of incubation. The DNA was codon-optimized for expression in E.coli and synthesized by the Korean company Bioneer Corporation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lei Sun

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: RhlR+C4
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Promoter activated by RhlR in concert with C4-HSL. C4-HSL is produced by RhlI, and acts as a quorum-sensing autoinducer.

This is the natural sequence taken from Pseudomonas aeruginosa.

Crosstalk: this promoter is also activated at a low level by LasR with its associated HSL.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
The -10 and -35 sites are labeled as identified in [Pearson97].

The part begins with the RhlR binding site, and (rather arbitrarily) ends with the first transcribed base (+1).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ronny Krashinsky
